MCCONNELLSBURG 2, EVERETT 0 >> McConnellsburg scored a goal in each half to ensure a Sideling Hill League victory over Everett. 
The Spartans (13-1, 9-1 SHL) came out of the gate strong with a goal from Patrick Keefer in the fourth minute of play. Jake Boehme then scored an insurance tally midway through the second half. 
"I thought Everett played us pretty tough this evening," McConnellsburg coach Cory Houck said. "They kept the pressure on our midfield. Our defense did a good job of holding off the fast breakaway this evening." 
Hunter Souders had three saves to preserve the shutout. McConnellsburg 2, Everett 0
